Dr '''Alison Morrison-Low''' is a retired Principal Curator for Science at [[National Museums Scotland]].

== Background ==
Morrison-Low is a director for the [[Brisbane Observatory]] Trust<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.secretscotland.org.uk/index.php/Secrets/BrisbaneObservatory |title=Brisbane Observatory |publisher=Secret Scotland |date= |accessdate=2016-12-10}}</ref> and has been a director for the Northern Lighthouse Heritage Trust, the British Society For The History Of Science and the [[Museum of Scottish Lighthouses]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.directorstats.co.uk/director/alison-morrison-low/ |title=Dr Alison Morrison-low, director at Brisbane Observatory Trust, Edinburgh |publisher=Directorstats |date= |accessdate=2016-12-10}}</ref>

In July 2016 she was an invited expert on for "The Invention of Photography", [[In Our Time (radio series)|In Our Time]], [[BBC Radio 4]].<ref>{{cite web|author=21:30 |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b07j699g |title=BBC Radio 4 - In Our Time, The Invention of Photography |publisher=BBC |date=2016-07-07 |accessdate=2016-12-10}}</ref> She won the [[Saltire Society Literary Awards|Saltire Society Research Book Prize]] in 2005 for "Weights and Measures in Scotland: A European Perspective", and in 2008 the Hans R. Jenemann Foundation's [[Paul Bunge]] Prize in 2008 for "Making Scientific Instruments in the Industrial Revolution".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=mersenne;40e93a7b.1506 |title=MERSENNE Archives |publisher=JISC |date=2015-06-17 |accessdate=2016-12-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/stereoscopy/0/steps/16684 |title=Stereoscopy |publisher=The University of Edinburgh |date=2016-12-05 |accessdate=2016-12-10}}</ref>

In 2018 Morrison-Low became the first female president of the [[Royal Scottish Society of Arts|Royal Scottish Society of the Arts]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rssa.org.uk/governance/council.shtml|title=RSSA Officers - 198th Session|website=www.rssa.org.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-07-24}}</ref>

