'''Downie bodies''', also known as a type of A-type inclusion,<ref name="isbn3-8055-2203-7">{{cite book |author=Cheville, Norman F. |title=Cytopathology in Viral Diseases (Monographs in Virology) |publisher=S.Karger AG |location= |year=1975 |pages=4 |isbn=3-8055-2203-7 |oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref> are a type of [[inclusion body]] associated with [[cowpox]].<ref name="pmid16200143">{{cite journal |author=Riedel S |title=Smallpox and biological warfare: a disease revisited |journal=Proc (Bayl Univ Med Cent) |volume=18 |issue=1 |pages=13–20 |date=January 2005 |pmid=16200143 |pmc=1200695 |doi= |url=}}</ref>

They are named for [[Allan Watt Downie]].

