'''Robert Banks''' (late 18th century-first half 19th century) was an English maker of optical instruments.

His workshop was located in the [[Strand, London|Strand]], in central [[London]], 1796-1827. The [[Museo di Fisica e Storia Naturale]] of [[Florence]] commissioned several optical instruments from him.

